parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of electrical switches can cause various safety-related issues, such as loss of turn signals, horn, and engine control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Turn signals will not turn off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of throttle control can cause sudden loss of power, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: engine going into emergency operation mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended left drift or pull can cause the motorcycle to veer into oncoming traffic, leading to potential accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It also leads to rider fatigue, discomfort, and distraction due to constant counter-steering.
symptoms: The motorcycle drifts or pulls to the left while in motion
requiring constant steering input to the right to counteract the pull

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump flange can cause gasoline to leak onto the engine and exhaust pipes, creating a high risk of fire.
symptoms: Gasoline leaks from the fuel pump flange
spraying gasoline onto the engine and exhaust pipes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of recall parts can lead to delays in repairing the fuel system, potentially causing fuel leaks, fires, or explosions, which can result in serious injuries or fatalities.
